"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78873","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-01","<p>Colombia, Peru, Panama and the region of Central America have recently negotiated access to the EU sugar market through their Free Trade Agreements.</p><p>UK sugar cane refiners also benefit from duty free access to sugar imports from Least Developed Countries under the Everything But Arms Agreement (EBA) and the EU’s Economic Partnership Agreements (EPAs) with African, Caribbean and Pacific countries. From 2009 these agreements have increased the quantity of cane sugar which can be imported duty-free.</p><p>EPA negotiations between the EU and Southern Africa were recently concluded and we expect this EPA to provide UK sugar cane refiners with improved access to cane sugar from Swaziland and South Africa. In addition, the recently negotiated EU-Fiji EPA should also allow UK firms to continue to buy duty-free Fijian cane sugar.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-01T13:04:43.0144073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78873/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78873/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-18","Cane Sugar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what progress has been made on ensuring that UK sugar cane refiners have improved access to cane sugar through free trade deals.","false","Biography information for Nigel Mills","Amber Valley","Nigel Mills","206599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78874","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>The decision to limit the allocation of shares under the Royal Mail Retail Offer to those applying for less than £10,000 was taken by Ministers on 9 October 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The banks involved in the sale of Royal Mail shares were informed on the same day as the decision was made.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","206647","2014-09-01T13:41:34.6080604Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78874/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78874/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-18","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, on what date the decision was taken to set the limit the public offering of Royal Mail shares to those applying for shares of a value of less than £10,000.","false","Biography information for Dr Alasdair McDonnell","Belfast South","Dr Alasdair McDonnell","206646"
