"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78925","Home Office","false","2014-08-04","<p>On 16 June 2014 the Home Secretary announced the introduction of the British-Irish Visa Scheme. From Autumn 2014, Chinese and Indian nationals with a visit visa issued in China and India respectively will be able to use an Irish visa to travel to the UK and a British visa to travel to Ireland without the need for a separate visa. This is underpinned by a range of detailed implementation activity.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-08-04T15:39:51.5202527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78925/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78925/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-18","Entry Clearances: Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what progress she has made on the detailed implementation of the proposed British-Irish visa scheme.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","206666"
