"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78764","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>Navigational lights will be installed on natural obstacles within the national conservation areas on the island.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The navigational lights will be located at The Barn, Great Stone Top, Horse Point, Bencoolen, and King and Queen’s Rocks. All of these areas are within the Airport Development Area agreed by St Helena Government.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-07-22T15:44:28.0600079Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78764/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78764/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-17","St Helena","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether there are any plans for beacons associated with airport construction on St Helena to be located within national conservation areas on the island.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","206529"
