"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78783","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-30","<p>I have spoken to many business groups and employers who tell me about how the compensation culture is tying their business in knots. Employers often do the right thing, put sensible safety procedures in place, and then someone does something daft and the employer still finds himself facing a negligence claim. The Bill should reassure employers and others that the courts will always consider the context of their actions before making a decision on liability. It should also deter claimants from bringing unfounded claims in the first place thereby helping to reduce insurance premiums. We have published an impact assessment at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/social-action-responsibility-and-heroism-bill#impact-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/social-action-responsibility-and-heroism-bill#impact-assessment</a></p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","206453 ; 206496","2014-07-30T15:42:37.9703737Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78783/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78783/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-17","Social Action, Responsibility and Heroism Bill","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of whether the bringing into force of the provisions of the Social Action, Responsibility and Heroism Bill will lead to fewer successful claims for damages under the current negligence laws.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Mr Andy Slaughter","206449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78784","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-30","<p>I have spoken to many business groups and employers who tell me about how the compensation culture is tying their business in knots. Employers often do the right thing, put sensible safety procedures in place, and then someone does something daft and the employer still finds himself facing a negligence claim. The Bill should reassure employers and others that the courts will always consider the context of their actions before making a decision on liability. It should also deter claimants from bringing unfounded claims in the first place thereby helping to reduce insurance premiums. We have published an impact assessment at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/social-action-responsibility-and-heroism-bill#impact-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/social-action-responsibility-and-heroism-bill#impact-assessment</a></p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","206449 ; 206496","2014-07-30T15:42:38.0693293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78784/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78784/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-17","Social Action, Responsibility and Heroism Bill","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the likely reduction in insurance premiums as a result of the Social Action, Responsibility and Heroism Bill.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Mr Andy Slaughter","206453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78785","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-09-01","<p>HM Prison Service operates an audit assurance mechanism to monitor prison security performance against national standards. On a yearly basis Internal Audit and Assurance Group visit each establishment to measure the effectiveness of local policies and procedures and award a rating according to the level of assurance gained.</p><p> </p><p>HMP Dartmoor received a security audit between the 24<sup>th</sup> and the 28<sup>th</sup> February 2014. The establishment was awarded the maximum possible green rating for all security modules assessed. Across recent audits HMP Dartmoor has received a green rating for all modules measuring the effectiveness of measures for preventing the conveyance of illicit articles.</p><p> </p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2014-09-01T16:20:57.5323126Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78785/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78785/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-17","Dartmoor Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the efficacy of measures to prevent drugs being smuggled into HM Prison Dartmoor.","false","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter","206459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78786","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-25","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service published a six-week consultation on the future of Spalding Magistrates’ Court on 1 July 2014 with an accompanying Impact Assessment. This court has been unoccupied and unused since January 2014. HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service has received no complaints from witnesses or parties travelling to other courts since this time.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p><p>The consultation, which closes on 12 August 2014, provides all court users with the opportunity to raise any concerns they may have about the proposals, including the impact the potential closure could have on travel distances.</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The Lord Chancellor will take into account all responses before any decision is made on the future of the court.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-07-25T12:08:10.6744109Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78786/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78786/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-17","Magistrates' Courts: Spalding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he has made an estimate of the number of people who will be resident 15 or more miles away from their nearest magistrates' court as a result of the closure of Spalding magistrates' courts.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Mr Andy Slaughter","206417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78787","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>Horrific offences took place at Kincora Boys Home in Belfast which were the subject of criminal prosecutions and a judge-led inquiry.</p><p>The new inquiry announced by my Rt hon Friend the Home Secretary on 7th July is currently being set up and its terms of reference are yet to be determined. My Rt hon Friend and I will consider carefully the representations made to it regarding its remit.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-07-22T11:06:47.690448Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78787/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78787/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-17","Kincora Children's Home","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if she will commission a Northern Ireland-based inquiry on child abuse at Kincora; and if she will include it in either the current inquiry in Northern Ireland or the national inquiry into abuse in care homes.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","206425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78788","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>My Department endeavours to answer all correspondence within the required performance targets. According to last year’s statistics my Department increased its response times by 21%.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-09-02T14:51:32.7450681Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78788/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78788/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-17","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether she has any plans to increase the number of replies within her Department's working day standard; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","206477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78789","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-22","<p>I wrote to the organisers of the petition on 15 January 2014. I understand the strength of feeling for the return of the Varosha area of Famagusta. The present state of that once-bustling town and nearby port reflects the consequences of the continued division of Cyprus.</p><p>We fully support all relevant Security Council resolutions, including Resolutions 550 and 789 which address the future of Varosha. We have raised this issue with the Turkish Cypriots and with the Turkish authorities. I remain convinced that, ultimately, a comprehensive settlement is the best chance of resolving this complex issue. The UK will continue to support the negotiations for a settlement, which will also address the question of Varosha.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-07-22T15:33:14.7785879Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78789/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78789/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-17","Cyprus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what response the Government has made to the petition presented to 10 Downing Street on 9 December 2013 on the return of Famagusta to its lawful inhabitants and the opening of the city's seaport; and what steps the UK is taking to support the return of that city to its former inhabitants.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","206576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78790","Scotland Office","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Scotland Office has a 15 working day target for responding to correspondence. Performance in meeting the target is kept under regular review by Ministers and senior management.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-07-22T14:06:48.67055Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78790/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78790/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-07-17","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether he has any plans to increase the number of replies within his Department's working day standard; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","206480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78791","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Department aims to maintain or improve upon the current high levels of performance. In 2013 Ministers responded to 97% of correspondence from MPs and Peers within the Department’s working day standard. Officials responded to 97% of correspondence from members of the public within the working day standard in 2013/14.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-07-22T14:37:19.1961357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78791/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78791/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has any plans to increase the number of replies within his Department's working day standard; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","206482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78792","Department for Transport","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport holds this information on a commercially confidential basis. However, as I stated in the debate of 16 July, Official Report, column 984, I am happy to consider whether the Department can release such information and I will meet with the Hon. Member and other Hon. Members for the local area shortly.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-09-02T14:14:29.7646535Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78792/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78792/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the passenger figures are for each of the last five years for the Transpennine Cleethorpes to Manchester service; and what information is held on the number of people who (a) alight and (b) board in (i) Doncaster and (ii) Sheffield.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","206419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78793","Department for Transport","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>The funding provided by the Department for W-Fi on-board trains is commercially sensitive information. Releasing it has the potential to impact the commercial arrangements between train operators and their suppliers. The Department does not fund any track side wi-fi infrastructure. Network Rail are looking to develop a commercial case for any service of this type.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-09-01T13:46:30.9348273Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78793/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78793/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the total annual public investment in (a) on train wi-fi services and (b) track side wi-fi infrastructure will be in each year from 2014 to 2019.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78794","Department for Transport","false","2014-09-01","<p>The Department has not made any estimates for this type of investment.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-09-01T13:45:17.7848177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78794/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78794/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of annual private investment in (a) on train wif-fi services and (b) track side wi-fi infrastructure in each year of Control Period 5 2015 to 2019.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78795","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Secretary of State and Ministerial colleagues meet regularly with senior officials from all three organisations, and issues concerning punctuality during Control Period 4 were frequently discussed during the course of that period.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-07-22T15:02:20.0242098Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78795/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78795/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he last discussed Network Rail's punctuality performance in Control Period 4 2009-14 with (a) Network Rail, (b) the Association of Train Operating Companies and (c) other members of the Rail Delivery Group.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78796","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Department has committed to undertaking six feasibility studies as part of the process of identifying and funding solutions to tackle some of the most notorious and long-standing road hot spots in the country, including the A303/A30/A358 corridor.</p><p> </p><p>In April this year, the Department published details of the scope, timing and management arrangement of the A303/A30/A358 feasibility study which is available from the Department for Transport website. The aim of the study is to identify the opportunities and understand the case for future investment solutions on the A303/A30/A358 corridor that are deliverable, affordable and offer value for money. The study is considering a range of solutions to the problems identified along the route, including to the problems identified on the sections between Amesbury and Honiton.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has committed to report back at Autumn Statement 2014 with solutions to the problems on this route, and through this feasibility study we will identify potential future investment proposals as part of our process for longer term investment planning.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-07-22T15:20:29.9212444Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78796/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78796/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","A303","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to ensure that the A303 is dualled from Honiton to Amesbury within the next 10 years.","false","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter","206458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78797","Department for Transport","false","2014-09-02","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department cannot release this information as it is commercially sensitive.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-09-02T15:31:47.9527621Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78797/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78797/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the annual investment of each franchised train operating company in wi-fi services has been since the start of each franchise agreement with his Department.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78798","Department for Transport","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>The funding will be ring fenced for investment into train borne WiFi systems.</p><p>We are still developing the mechanisms by which we will administer the funding, and will be in a position to give further information in September 2014.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-09-01T13:48:10.4738124Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78798/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78798/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how (a) his Department and (b) the Office of Rail Regulation will distribute to train operating companies funds for investment in free passenger wi-fi on train services from the fine on Network Rail for punctuality performance; and whether those funds will be ringfenced.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78799","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p /><p>The criteria for establishing delay causes are to be found in the Delay Attribution Guide, issued by the Delay Attribution Board – a joint rail industry body remitted to provide guidance to the industry on delay attribution issues.</p><p>The current guide was issued in April 2014. Copies of the all the guides since 2007 can be seen at:</p><p /> <p> </p><p><a href="http://www.delayattributionboard.co.uk/delayattributionguides.htm" target="_blank">http://www.delayattributionboard.co.uk/delayattributionguides.htm</a></p><p>The Department does not make estimates with regard to the attribution of delay in respect of the annual number of timetabled passenger train services that arrived, either within 5 minutes or not, of their scheduled arrival time.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The industry uses the Delay Attribution Guide to attribute delays by total minutes of delay, not by number of trains. The Office of Rail Regulation is beginning to publish such information; see</p><p /> <p> </p><p><a href="http://orr.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0004/13792/network-rail-monitor-2013-14-q4.pdf" target="_blank">http://orr.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0004/13792/network-rail-monitor-2013-14-q4.pdf</a> (page11) for the 2013-14 figures as to how industry delay was apportioned for each operator and nationally.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","206435","2014-07-22T15:18:14.5585057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78799/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78799/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what criteria are used to establish whether delays over five minutes to a timetabled long distance train service are caused by (a) Network Rail, (b) the train operating company or (c) other factors; and what changes have been made to those criteria since January 2008.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78800","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Office of Rail Regulation are an independent statutory body, with powers vested by Parliament in their board. As an independent regulator, the ORR operates within the framework set by UK and EU legislation and is accountable through Parliament and the courts.</p><p>As announced in 2012 (see <a href="http://orr.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0004/13792/network-rail-monitor-2013-14-q4.pdf" target="_blank">http://orr.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0004/13792/network-rail-monitor-2013-14-q4.pdf</a> for details)</p><p> </p><p>[the] <em>ORR’s Board issued an order that a reasonable sum of £1.5 million would be returned to funders at the end of CP4 for every 0.1 percentage point below the sector regulated target that Network Rail achieved. We have reviewed the available evidence and concluded that Network Rail did not do everything reasonably practicable to achieve the 2013-14 PPM target in the Long Distance sector, and determined that a reasonable sum of £76.8 million would apply. We adjusted the figure to take account of factors which were beyond Network Rail’s reasonable control including extreme weather, and external factors such as suicides and cable theft. The final sum is £53.1 million</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Ministers and Department officials were briefed by the ORR shortly before the issue of the 2012 order and the final decision on the amount payable, but were not party to either decision.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DfT Ministers and officials regularly meet with the Office of Rail Regulation to discuss Network Rail’s performance. ORR is the independent economic regulator accountable to parliament and ORR’s board makes its regulatory decisions independently of government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","206436 ; 206437","2014-07-22T15:14:41.7515388Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78800/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78800/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have had with the Office of Rail Regulation about the level of fine imposed on Network Rail for its punctuality performance in Control Period four 2009-14.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78801","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p /><p>The criteria for establishing delay causes are to be found in the Delay Attribution Guide, issued by the Delay Attribution Board – a joint rail industry body remitted to provide guidance to the industry on delay attribution issues.</p><p>The current guide was issued in April 2014. Copies of the all the guides since 2007 can be seen at:</p><p /> <p> </p><p><a href="http://www.delayattributionboard.co.uk/delayattributionguides.htm" target="_blank">http://www.delayattributionboard.co.uk/delayattributionguides.htm</a></p><p>The Department does not make estimates with regard to the attribution of delay in respect of the annual number of timetabled passenger train services that arrived, either within 5 minutes or not, of their scheduled arrival time.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The industry uses the Delay Attribution Guide to attribute delays by total minutes of delay, not by number of trains. The Office of Rail Regulation is beginning to publish such information; see</p><p /> <p> </p><p><a href="http://orr.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0004/13792/network-rail-monitor-2013-14-q4.pdf" target="_blank">http://orr.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0004/13792/network-rail-monitor-2013-14-q4.pdf</a> (page11) for the 2013-14 figures as to how industry delay was apportioned for each operator and nationally.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","206434","2014-07-22T15:18:14.6395206Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78801/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78801/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-17","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his most recent estimate is of the annual number of timetabled passenger train services that arrived (a) within five minutes of and (b) five minutes or more after the scheduled time due to factors attributable to the franchised train operating company in each year since 2004.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","206435"
