"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78804","Wales Office","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>The Wales Office has a 15 working day target for responding to correspondence. The Office responded to 98% of all correspondence within the working day standard in 2013-2014.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2014-09-02T15:39:01.3508845Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78804/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78804/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-07-17","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, whether he has any plans to increase the number of replies within his Department's working day standard; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","206473"
