"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78812","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-22","<p>The remit of the Wood Review on maximising economic recovery was to consider how economic recovery of oil and gas could be maximised from the UK Continental Shelf. In doing so, the review did not directly cover health and safety. In maximising economic recovery from the UK Continental Shelf, industry will continue to be required to fully comply with all health and safety legislation.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","206448","2014-07-22T12:07:24.7660352Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78812/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78812/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78812/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-07-17","Offshore Industry: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the potential effects of the introduction of (a) the Government's strategy for maximising economic recovery from the UK continental shelf and (b) the Oil and Gas Authority will have on the safety of offshore oil gas workers.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","206508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78813","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-22","<p /> <p /> <p>The PIP Assessment Guide for Health Professionals carrying out assessments includes guidance on the assessment criteria and how they should be applied. This guidance can be accessed on the gov.uk website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210722/pip-assessment-guide.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210722/pip-assessment-guide.pdf</a>.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-07-22T11:21:56.1935273Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78813/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78813/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78813/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-17","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will publish the guidance issued by his Department to Atos Healthcare on Part 2, Regulation 7 of the Social Security (Personal Independence Payment) Regulations 2013.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","206501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78814","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-22","<p /> <p /> <p>The information requested is not available. The Personal Independence Payment statistics release strategy, which the Department has made available on Gov.Uk, explains how DWP will manage the release of statistics and related information on Personal Independence Payment. This document explained that future releases may be extended to include numbers of reconsideration and appeals.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice publish Tribunal quarterly statistics on Gov.Uk, this includes information on appeals against PIP decisions.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-07-22T11:26:51.9398697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78814/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78814/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78814/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-17","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of new claims for personal independence payments that were refused on application were subsequently allowed on appeal in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","206502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78815","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-22","<p /> <p /> <p>Statistics on the number of claims outstanding are not routinely derived or published.</p><p>PIP statistics published on 5th June 2014 showed that by the end of March 2014, 349,000 PIP new claims had been registered and 83,900 PIP new claim decisions had been made. There are several reasons why a registered claim may not yet be determined. For example the claimant has not yet returned their additional information form or is awaiting their assessment date, DWP have not yet made a decision on their claim or the claimant has advised that they wish to withdraw their claim.<strong>    </strong></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-07-22T11:31:32.4136623Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78815/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78815/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78815/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-17","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many new claims for personal independence payments are outstanding.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","206503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78816","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-22","<p /> <p /> <p>The available information on successful claims to personal independence payment was published on 5 June and is available from the gov.uk website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/personal-independence-payment-official-statistics-june-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/personal-independence-payment-official-statistics-june-2014</a>.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-07-22T12:02:31.6273257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78816/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78816/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78816/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-17","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of new claims for personal independence payments have been successful since April 2013.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","206504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78817","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-22","<p /> <p>Statistics on clearance times are intended for future publication and the Department's analysts are currently considering what information will be included in the release.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-07-22T11:38:52.2945391Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78817/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78817/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78817/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-17","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many new claimants of persoanl independence payment have not received a decision within 26 weeks of the date of their claim.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","206505"
